\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 thereby represents the proportion of rides starting at the station represented
 by the column that end at the station represented by the row.
 For example, the 
\begin_inset Formula $0.06937$
\end_inset

 in the first row, third column means that 6.937% of rides starting at station
 number 31043 end at station number 31041.
 In other words, about 7% of the bikes at station number 31043 are destined
 for station number 31041.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Multiplying 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{2,1}M_{1,5}$
\end_inset

 then represents the percentage of bikes at the station of column 2 (31042)
 that are destined for the station of column 5 (31045) via the station of
 column 1 (31041).
 Similarly, 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{2,2}M_{2,5}$
\end_inset

